Enclosing class:
ORTree
public class ORTree.IndexEntry
extends Tree.IndexEntry

This class describes the index entries (i.e. the entries of the non-leaf nodes) of a tree. Each index entry refers to a node which is the root of the subtree. We call this node the subnode of the index entry.

See Also:

initialize

public Tree.IndexEntry initialize(Tree.Node.SplitInfo splitInfo)
Initializes the (new) IndexEntry using some split information. The default implementation calls super.initialize(splitInfo) and initializes the descriptor of the index entry by {ORTree.Node.SplitInfo#newDescriptor() the new descriptor of the splitInfo}.

Overrides:
initialize in class Tree.IndexEntry
Parameters:
